\textbf{Full-Solution Problem.} Justify your answer and \textbf{show all
your work.} Simplification of your answer is not required.

Let $\displaystyle R$ be the finite region bounded above by the curve

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle y = 4 - x^{2}
\end{align*} and bounded below by

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle y = 2-x.
\end{align*} Carefully sketch $\displaystyle R$ and find
its area explicitly.
